Erik Tveraaen Torvbr√•ten

Who am I?

I am a 22 year old man from Asker Norway. Currently I am on my third year of a MSc degree in computer science at the norwegian university of science and technology NTNU with specialization in software development. I have a strong interest in technology and innovation and how we can take advantage of new technologies in companies and in the society. I started programming in 2020 and I really enjoy developing my CS skills and learning new concepts. I am also interested in finance and economics, and I have always had a strong interest in social economics.

I am an outgoing person who loves to work with people. I am

Education

- Completed three years of a MSc degree in Computer Science at NTNU

- Asker upper secondary school, graduated in 2019

Work

- Summer sales staff at IKEA, summer of 2021 and 2022

- Squad leader in the norwegian air force during my initial service, 2019 - 2020

Voluntary Work

- Abakus, finance and banking committee, 2022 -

- Engineers Without Borders,

{/*the black and white piocture*/}

So what have I learned?

{/*where I write about what my education and work has tought me*/}

Computer Science

Throughout my studies I have learned how to approach difficult problems. I have completed courses in mathematics, algorithms, computer architecture, software development, object oriented programming, design principles and much more. I have gained a lot of experience programming in java and python, and especially object oriented programming in java, with and without the spring framework. I also know how to work with SQL databases. The last year I have also been interested in javascript and the react framework. I have basic knowledge about C from computer architecture and operating system classes. The last year I have also learned about project management and the Scrum framework. I have gained experience with Scrum from two group projects and the process of creating good software.

Work and Voluntary Work

Learning to work efficently with other people is the most valuable skill I have developed when working. I like having responsability and I enjoy being able to influence decisions. During my inital service I gained experience in team management as a squad leader. At IKEA I gained experience in sales and logistics. From EWB I worked as an event planner to increase the awarness of the importance of aid and how we can use engineering in aid work. I learned a lot about planning, communicating with others and how to arrange good events. I did not have any interst in aid before I joined EWB, but I though that if I was going to use my free time working, it should be for a good cause. I became more aware of how our actions can have a positive impact on other people from less prosporus countries. After my year at EWB I was encouraged to apply for several board member positions. I took what I learned from EWB and applyed for a position in the finance and banking committee in Abakus. I wanted to gain experience with finance and I hope that I will continue to develop myself at Abakus the next year.
